President Obama has declared a major disaster in Texas and authorized federal aid to assist with recovery efforts following an explosion that occurred between April 17-20, 2013. The federal funding will be available to state and local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, to help with emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Kevin L. Hannes has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@DHS.GOV.